                  , from his person
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>GEORGE LAURENCE. I am employed as a <rs id="t18300415-346-viclabel1872" type="occupation">warehouseman</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-346-victim2856 t18300415-346-viclabel1872"></join>, in Cheapside. On the 8th of April, a little after nine o'clock in the evening. I was in <placeName id="t18300415-346-crimeloc1873">Aldersgate-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-346-crimeloc1873" type="placeName" value="Aldersgate-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-346-crimeloc1873" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-346-off1870 t18300415-346-crimeloc1873"></join>, and the officer accosted me - I went back with him, and he took the prisoner a few yards off - I saw him find my handkerchief in his pocket; he said nothing - I had not felt it taken, but had used it a very few minutes before.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-346-person2857">
                  THOMAS 
                  BICKNELL
               <interp inst="t18300415-346-person2857" type="surname" value="BICKNELL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-346-person2857" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-346-person2857" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. On the 8th of April, about nine o'clock in the evening, I saw the prisoner in company with another lad - I observed the prisoner put his hand into Laurence's pocket, and take out the handkerchief; I followed Laurence, brought him back, and found the prisoner with his hand in another<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183004150145"></xptr>gentleman's pocket, at the very moment, in the act of taking another handkerchief - I took his companion, but he was discharged: I found the prosecutor's handkerchief in the prisoner's pocket.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I had been out of place for six months - I have no father; I was trying for fifteen weeks to go to the Marine Society, but was refused by the doctor; I was told if I committed any act, that would send me there, or to the Refuge - I should be happy to get my living honestly.</p>
               <p>THOMAS BICKNELL. I found his statement, about the Marine Society, true - his companion was thirteen years old.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 17. - <rs id="t18300415-346-verdict1874" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18300415-346-verdict1874" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               Judgment Respited
            </rs>
